# fusion-box wine patch 0009
# Sync wl_subsurface positions for all SUBSURFACE-role children of a toplevel
# at the toplevel's own commit, instead of relying on each child's
# reconfigure_subsurface gate.
#
# Bug - right-edge artifact "echoes" on horizontal-shrink window resize.
# After dragging the right edge of the Fusion window leftward (making the
# window narrower), residual pixels from sub-widgets (Browser sidebar,
# Comments panel, ribbon-area widgets) remained visible past the new
# right edge of the window. Clicking inside the window eventually
# dismissed them. Vertical resize was clean, left-to-right grow was
# clean - only right-to-left shrink misbehaved.
#
# Root cause - position update gate misses non-role-change paths:
#
# Subsurface child positions update via wayland_surface_reconfigure_subsurface
# (wayland_surface.c:920), which is gated on
# `surface->processing.serial && surface->processing.processed`. Those flags
# are set only in wayland_win_data_update_wayland_state for the SUBSURFACE
# role, which is itself called only from wayland_win_data_create_wayland_surface
# (window.c:899) - i.e., on role-change paths. Non-role-change
# WAYLAND_WindowPosChanged events (which is what fires during user-driven
# resize as Qt repositions widgets to track main's new layout) leave the gate
# closed: wl_subsurface_set_position never gets called, the subsurface stays
# at its last reconfigured local position.
#
# When main shrinks horizontally, ordinary sibling subsurfaces (Browser
# sidebar at right side of main, Comments panel, ribbon-area pieces) stay at
# their OLD x positions in main's coordinate system. Per xdg-shell spec,
# `xdg_surface.set_window_geometry` informs the compositor of the window's
# logical bounds but is NOT a clipping mask for subsurfaces - subsurfaces
# extend freely past it. So KWin renders the stale-positioned sibling
# subsurfaces past main's new (narrower) right edge as visible "echo"
# artifacts.
#
# A click in the window triggers Qt to repaint widgets via WM_PAINT, which
# fires set_window_surface_contents for each affected widget; the role-change
# path doesn't run, but the iteration in set_window_surface_contents for main
# (patch 0006's vsub iteration loop) DOES eventually walk the rb tree -
# patch 0006's filter excludes non-vsubs, but its presence shows the right
# hook point exists.
#
# Fix - extend patch 0006's vsub iteration to also update non-vsub
# SUBSURFACE child positions, and commit main again at end of iteration:
#
# 1. **New branch at top of patch 0006's RB_FOR_EACH_ENTRY loop**: for each
#    SUBSURFACE-role child of `hwnd` (the toplevel committing in this
#    set_window_surface_contents call) that is NOT a virtual_buffer vsub,
#    look up its current screen rect via NtUserGetWindowRect, compute
#    local position by subtracting toplevel_rect, and call
#    wl_subsurface_set_position. Continue to skip the vsub-specific
#    processing below for this entry. Same coord calc as patch 0006 already
#    uses for vsubs (`NtUserGetWindowRect` is screen-relative for any HWND
#    - reliable across deeply nested WS_CHILD chains where `data->rects.window`
#    would be PARENT-relative and wrong).
#
# 2. **Second wl_surface_commit on main** at end of iteration: the first
#    main commit at line 1280 already attached the buffer for this frame.
#    The position updates we just queued (both from the non-vsub branch and
#    the vsub iteration's existing wl_subsurface_set_position calls) are
#    pending on main's wl_surface. A second commit on main applies them
#    atomically - no new buffer attach, no damage, just commits queued
#    subsurface state. Without this, queued positions hang until Qt
#    happens to trigger another main paint (lazy after resize ends);
#    artifact echoes persist until click. With this, the positions apply on
#    the same frame and KWin re-renders the scene correctly within the
#    same paint cycle.
#
# Coverage verified (2026-06-11):
#   - Horizontal-shrink artifacts: fixed - artifacts now self-correct
#     within a few frames; no click required to dismiss.
#   - Horizontal-grow: clean (was clean before).
#   - Vertical-grow: clean (was clean before).
#   - Sketch enter/exit, scroll, etc.: no regression - patch 0008's
#     coverage unaffected.
#
# NOT fixed by this patch (separate bugs, documented in docs/observed-issues.md):
#   - Vertical-shrink timeline disappearance: same gate root cause but the
#     trigger is different. Specifically, the timeline is a Qt6 native
#     toplevel-like widget (selfroot in Win32, but a SUBSURFACE child of
#     main in Wayland terms) whose Win32 position is updated by Qt's
#     deferred-layout system - which doesn't necessarily call SetWindowPos
#     on every pixel of resize. Even with our walk reading
#     NtUserGetWindowRect, we read Qt's last-set position which may be
#     stale relative to main's current height. The fix is plausibly
#     Qt-side (force-synchronous layout during WM_SIZE) rather than wine-
#     side. Investigated 2026-06-11 evening: tried QT_USE_NATIVE_WINDOWS=1,
#     QT_QPA_UPDATE_IDLE_TIME=0, QT_NO_FAST_MOVE=1 - no effect. Wine-side
#     plateau reached on this specific bug; Qt build infra investment
#     would be needed for further progress.
#   - Vertical-shrink navbar-blank-white: navbar's wl_subsurface position
#     is correct (visible at right location) but content is blank.
#     Mechanism is patch 0006's wp_viewport crop from main's GDI buffer
#     sees a region Qt hasn't fully painted yet during rapid resize. The
#     navbar widget itself paints into main's GDI; if Qt's paint events
#     are batched/deferred, wine flushes incomplete buffer to vsub.
#     Likely same root layer (Qt deferred paint timing) as the timeline
#     bug. Not addressed here.
#
# Status: verified 2026-06-11 against Fusion 360 v2703.1.11 on KDE Plasma 6
# Wayland with NVIDIA Open 610.43.02. Horizontal shrink artifacts self-
# correct without click. No regression on prior coverage.
#
# Upstream: candidate for wine-devel submission. The change is small (~30
# lines, two hunks both inside set_window_surface_contents) and
# architecturally clean - it extends the existing per-toplevel-commit
# iteration that patch 0006 already established. The argument: any
# Qt6-style application with multiple non-vsub subsurface children that
# move during parent resize will see this class of bug; we're closing
# the gate-misses-position-updates path that existing code only handles
# on role changes.
#
# Apply from the wine source root: `patch -p1 < this-file`. Depends on
# patches 0001-0008 (line offsets assume all are applied).
#
# Author: fusion-box (claude-code session, with Barrett Otte)
#
--- a/dlls/winewayland.drv/window.c
+++ b/dlls/winewayland.drv/window.c
@@ -1270,6 +1270,30 @@
                 RECT child_screen, child_local;
                 int sx, sy, sw, sh;

+                /* fusion-box patch 0009: queue wl_subsurface_set_position for
+                 * non-vsub SUBSURFACE children of this toplevel. Unified with
+                 * vsub processing below: vsubs (patch 0006) need full buffer
+                 * attach; non-vsubs just need position update. Both share the
+                 * toplevel_rect for screen-to-local conversion. Without this,
+                 * ordinary subsurface positions only update via
+                 * reconfigure_subsurface, gated on processing.serial - set only
+                 * on role-change paths. Fixes Browser/Comments/ribbon-area
+                 * subsurfaces showing as right-edge artifacts during horizontal
+                 * shrink resize. */
+                if (!child->virtual_buffer && parent_ok && (cs = child->wayland_surface)
+                    && cs->wl_subsurface
+                    && cs->role == WAYLAND_SURFACE_ROLE_SUBSURFACE
+                    && cs->toplevel_hwnd == hwnd
+                    && NtUserGetWindowRect(child->hwnd, &child_screen, 0))
+                {
+                    int local_x = child_screen.left - toplevel_rect.left;
+                    int local_y = child_screen.top  - toplevel_rect.top;
+                    TRACE("[fusion-box-patch0009] sub_pos hwnd=%p local=(%d,%d)\n",
+                          child->hwnd, local_x, local_y);
+                    wl_subsurface_set_position(cs->wl_subsurface, local_x, local_y);
+                    continue;
+                }
+
                 if (!child->virtual_buffer) continue;
                 if (child->virtual_toplevel != hwnd) continue;
                 seen++;
@@ -1354,6 +1378,12 @@
             if (seen > 0)
                 TRACE("[fusion-box-vsub] parent_commit hwnd=%p seen=%d committed=%d skipped=%d\n",
                     hwnd, seen, committed_vsubs, skipped);
+            /* fusion-box patch 0009: second commit on main to flush queued
+             * subsurface positions (from both the non-vsub branch above and
+             * any vsub set_position calls). Without this, queued positions
+             * hang until Qt happens to trigger another main paint. */
+            if (parent_ok && parent_surf && parent_surf->wl_surface)
+                wl_surface_commit(parent_surf->wl_surface);
             wl_display_flush(process_wayland.wl_display);
         }
         else
